[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 9/100 path 5/5 answer="Let's break down the problem:\n\n1. Initially, Brian has 20 video games.\n2. After losing 5, he now has 20 - 5 = 15 video games.\n3. According to the information given, Bobby has 5 fewer than 3 times as many video games as Brian does.\n   So, we calculate 3 times the number of Brian's remaining games:\n   3 × 15 = 45 video games.\n4. Now, we subtract 5 from this amount because Bobby has 5 fewer than 45:\n   45 - 5 = 40 video games.\n\nTherefore, Bobby has 40 video games."
