[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 24/100 done id=gsm8k_test_318 prediction='123' gold='123' correct=True vote_counts={'123': 3, "We start with the given information:\n- There are 3 times as many girls as boys.\n- There are 1/10 as many non-gendered children as boys.\n- The number of boys is 30.\n\nLet B represent the number of boys and G represent the number of girls. We know:\nB = 30\n\nSince there are 3 times as many girls as boys, we can write:\nG = 3 * B\n\nSubstituting B = 30 into the equation:\nG = 3 * 30 = 90\n\nSo now, we know there are 90 girls.\n\nNext, let's calculate the number of non-gendered children. Since there are 1/10 as many non-gendered children as boys, we can write:\nNGC = (1/10) * B\n\nSubstituting B = 30 into the equation:\nNGC = (1/10) * 30 = 3\n\nSo now, we know there are 3 non-gendered children.\n\nTo find the total number of children, we sum up all the individuals:\n\nTotal Children = Boys + Girls + Non-Gendered Children\n\nSubstituting the values we found:\nTotal Children = B + G + NGC\n              = 30 + 90 + 3\n              = 123\n\nTherefore, the total number of children is 123.": 1, '129': 1}
