[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 45/100 path 1/5 answer="Let's break it down step-by-step:\n\n1. **Calculate total savings required**: \n   \\[ \\text{Total Savings} = \\$1125 \\]\n\n2. **Identify the savings structure**:\n   - Let \\( S_1 \\) represent savings in the first half of the month (which we can assume starts on the 1st).\n   - Let \\( S_2 \\) represent savings in the second half of the month.\n\n3. **Given relationship between first and second halves**:\n   \\[ S_2 = 2 \\times S_1 \\]\n\n4. **Calculate savings in the first half of the month**:\n   \\[ S_1 + S_2 = \\$1125 \\]\n   Substitute \\( S_2 = 2S_1 \\):\n   \\[ S_1 + 2S_1 = \\$1125 \\]\n   Simplifying gives us:\n   \\[ 3S_1 = \\$1125 \\]\n   So,\n   \\[ S_1 = \\frac{\\$1125}{3} = \\$375 \\]\n\n5. **Determine savings in the second half**:\n   \\[ S_2 = 2S_1 = 2 \\times \\$375 = \\$750 \\]\n\n6. **Calculate number of days in the second half of the month**:\n   Assuming a typical month with 30 days:\n   \\[ \\text{Number of days in second half} = \\frac{30}{2} = 15 \\]\n\n7. **Calculate daily savings in the second half**:\n   \\[ \\text{Daily savings} = \\frac{S_2}{\\text{Number of days}} = \\frac{\\$750}{15} = \\$5"
