[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 71/100 path 1/5 answer="In the first place, we can determine how many burritos all the students received together:\nEach student got 10 burritos, so for 50 students, they would have gotten 50 × 10 = 500 burritos.\n\nNow, let's subtract the number of burritos Mr. George ate from the initial amount:\nGeorge ate 20 burritos, so subtracting these leaves us with 600 - 20 = 580 burritos remaining.\n\nFinally, we subtract the total number of burritos the students received from the remaining ones to find out how many were left over:\n580 - 500 = 80 burritos.\n\nTherefore, the total number of leftover burritos from the picnic is 80."
