[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 78/100 path 4/5 answer="Let \\( S \\) represent the number of small stuffed animals sold, and \\( L \\) represent the number of large stuffed animals sold. Given:\n1. Each small stuffed animal costs $4.\n2. Teresa sold twice as many small stuffed animals as large stuffed animals.\n3. She earned $120 from the sales.\n\nFirstly, let’s express the revenue from each type of stuffed animal:\n\nRevenue from small stuffed animals (\\( R_S \\)) can be calculated as follows:\n\\[ R_S = S \\times \\$4 \\]\n\nSince Teresa sold two times as many small stuffed animals as large stuffed animals:\n\\[ S = 2L \\]\n\nNext, let's determine the total revenue from both types of stuffed animals combined:\n\\[ \\text{Total Revenue} = R_S + 3R_L \\]\nwhere \\( R_L \\) represents the revenue from large stuffed animals.\n\nGiven the total earnings were $120:\n\\[ R_S + 3R_L = \\$120 \\]\n\nWe know:\n\\[ R_S = S \\times \\$4 \\]\nSubstitute \\( S = 2L \\):\n\\[ R_S = (2L) \\times \\$4 = \\$8L \\]\n\nTherefore,\n\\[ \\$8L + 3R_L = \\$120 \\]\n\nTo find \\( L \\), we first isolate \\( R_L \\):\n\\[ 3R_L = \\$120 - \\$8L \\]\n\\[ R_L = \\frac{\\$120 - \\$8L}{3} \\]\n\nNow, substituting back into the equation for total revenue:\n\\[ \\$8L + 3 \\left(\\frac{\\$120 - \\$8L}{3}\\right) = \\$120 \\]\nSimplify the expression inside the parentheses:\n\\[ \\$8L + (120 - 8L) = \\$1"
