[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 path 5/5 answer='First, we calculate how many groups of 8 crayons Nik can make from his 200 crayons:\n\\[ \\text{Number of groups} = \\frac{\\text{Total number of crayons}}{\\text{Crayons per group}} = \\frac{200}{8} = 25 \\text{ groups} \\]\n\nNext, we find out how many boxes these 25 groups will fill:\n\\[ \\text{Number of boxes} = \\text{Number of groups} = 25 \\]\n\nEach box weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the boxes is:\n\\[ \\text{Weight of boxes} = \\text{Number of boxes} \\times \\text{Weight per box} = 25 \\times 8 = 200 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\nTo convert ounces to pounds (since there are 16 ounces in a pound):\n\\[ \\text{Total weight in pounds} = \\frac{\\text{Weight in ounces}}{16} = \\frac{200}{16} = 12.5 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo, the total weight of the crayons and the boxes is:\n\\[ \\boxed{12.5} \\]'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 84/100 done id=gsm8k_test_1130 prediction='25' gold='25' correct=True vote_counts={'25': 2, '212.5': 1, '14.0625': 1, 'First, we calculate how many groups of 8 crayons Nik can make from his 200 crayons:\n\\[ \\text{Number of groups} = \\frac{\\text{Total number of crayons}}{\\text{Crayons per group}} = \\frac{200}{8} = 25 \\text{ groups} \\]\n\nNext, we find out how many boxes these 25 groups will fill:\n\\[ \\text{Number of boxes} = \\text{Number of groups} = 25 \\]\n\nEach box weighs 8 ounces, so the total weight of the boxes is:\n\\[ \\text{Weight of boxes} = \\text{Number of boxes} \\times \\text{Weight per box} = 25 \\times 8 = 200 \\text{ ounces} \\]\n\nTo convert ounces to pounds (since there are 16 ounces in a pound):\n\\[ \\text{Total weight in pounds} = \\frac{\\text{Weight in ounces}}{16} = \\frac{200}{16} = 12.5 \\text{ pounds} \\]\n\nSo, the total weight of the crayons and the boxes is:\n\\[ \\boxed{12.5} \\]': 1}
