[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 58/100 path 1/3 answer='First, let\'s calculate how many points each student has:\n\n1. Adam already has 50 points.\n\n2. Betty collected 30% more points than Adam:\n   30% of 50 = 0.30 * 50 = 15 points\n   So, Betty has 50 + 15 = 65 points.\n\n3. Marta collected 3 times more points than Tom:\n   Since Tom has 30 points, Marta has 3 * 30 = 90 points.\n\n4. Now we know that Betty (65) > Adam (50), so Betty is better than Adam.\n\nNext, we find out how many points Tom has:\n   Marta has 90 points, which is 3 times Tom\'s points,\n   Therefore, Tom has 90 / 3 = 30 points.\n\nNow, let\'s sum up all the points collected by the students:\n   Adam: 50 points\n   Betty: 65 points\n   Tom: 30 points\n   Martha: Not given directly but implied to have some points since it mentions "Marta" and "Tom"\n\nSince we don\'t have Martha\'s exact number of points, we\'ll assume she also follows the same pattern where she collects three times the amount of points Tom has, which is 30 points.\n\nSo, Martha has 30 points.\n\nAdding them together gives us the total points collected by the class:\n   Total points = Adam + Betty + Tom + Martha\n                = 50 + 65 + 30 + 30\n                = 175\n\nFinally, to determine how many points the class is missing to reach the trip threshold of 400 points:\n   Points needed = 400 - Total points collected\n                 ='
