the earnings equation:\n\n\\[ 4(2L) + 12L = 120 \\]\n\\[ 8L + 12L = 120 \\]\n\\[ 20L = 120 \\]\n\nNow solve for \\( L \\):\n\n\\[ L = \\frac{120}{20} \\]\n\\[ L = 6 \\]\n\nSo, Teresa sold 6 large stuffed animals.\n\nSince \\( S = 2L \\), we find \\( S \\):\n\n\\[ S = 2 \\times 6 \\]\n\\[ S = 12 \\]\n\nTherefore, Teresa sold 12 small stuffed animals today.': 1}
