[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 80/100 path 3/3 answer='To find the total area of the walls, we calculate the area of each pair of opposite walls:\nNorth wall + South wall: \\(10 \\times 8 = 80\\) square feet\nEast wall + West wall: \\(5 \\times 8 = 40\\) square feet\n\nAdding these together gives us the total area of all four walls:\n\\(80 + 40 = 120\\) square feet\n\nSince one gallon of paint covers 20 square feet, we divide the total area by the coverage of one gallon:\n\\(120 \\div 20 = 6\\) gallons needed\n\nGiven that each gallon costs $12, the total cost would be:\n\\(6 \\times 12 = \\$\\boxed{72}\\)'
